  "text": "Ross et al. [CITATION_1] investigated the relationship between vertebral body dimensions and FR in vivo. They analyzed h a /h p as the parameter describing vertebral shape in the LAT view and found that a smaller h a /h p ratio might increase fracture risk by shifting loads toward the anterior part of the vertebrae. They did not find a significant direct correlation between vertebral body heights or h a /h p with FR, which is in agreement with our results, as we did not observe a statistically significant correlation between h a /h p and F max (r = -0.236, p = 0.201) or P max (r = -0.146, p = 0.433).",
